oai_dc:dc.dc:title: THE COASTLINE OF RIVER-DELTAS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bakker, W.T.J.N.P.
Edelman, T.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: river delta
sediment transport by waves
coastline shape
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The purpose of this paper is to investigate the shape of the coastline of a river delta on a coast, along which sediment is transported by waves only. In order to make the problem suitable to a mathematical treatment it is necessary to simplify to a large extend the processes occurring in nature.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 9 (1964): Proceedings of 9th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Lisbon, Portugal, 1964.; 13
